


Instructions when running from floppy.

*****NOTE***** Use UPPER CASE COMMANDS ONLY!!

Use the following command format.

GAME (SWITCH1) (SWITCH2) (SWITCH3)



-------------------------------------------------------------
Switch 1 will determine your graphic card type.
These are the availible commands.

M - MCGA
E - EGA
T - Tandy 16
C - CGA
-------------------------------------------------------------



-------------------------------------------------------------
Switch 2 will determine your input type.
These are the avaible commands.

M - Mouse input.
K - Keyboard input.
-------------------------------------------------------------



-------------------------------------------------------------
Switch 3 will determine your sound card support.

R - Will support the Roland MT-32 or LAPC-1 sound card.
A - Will support Adlib or Soundblaster card.

If you do not have a sound card, do not use any switch.
------------------------------------------------------------


EXAMPLES:

GAME M M R .... Will run game with MCGA, MOUSE, and Roland.
GAME E K A .... Will run game with EGA, Keyboard, and Adlib.
GAME C K   .... Will run game with CGA, Keyboard, and no sound.



